body:
Example Code:

```
<div class="content">
    <img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1b/Square_200x200.png" width="200" height="100">
</div>
```

CSS
```
.Content {
    position:absolute;
    left:50%;
    top:50%;
    width:550px;
    height:350px;
    margin-top:-190px;
    margin-left:-275px;
    padding:15px;
}
```
 Step One: Center the div but div center is not the same as body center
```
.Content {
    position:absolute;
    left:50%;
    top:50%;
```

Step Two: Use negative margin to let the div center overlap with body center:
Fiddle example [Final Example](http://jsfiddle.net/chenhaoyu/ZLn9s/1/)
